title: Mini Windows XP SP3 Extremely Fast + Drivers [240MB]
description:
Mini Windows XP SP3 Extremely Fast + Drivers [240MB]

Microsoft Windows XP SP3 + SATA Drivers + Chipset Drivers
Windows XP is an operating system produced by Microsoft for use on personal computers, including home and business desktops, laptops, and media centers.

It was first released in August 2001, and is the most popular version of Windows, based on installed user base. The name "XP" is short for eXPerience.

Windows XP is the successor to both Windows 2000 and Windows Me, and is the first consumer-oriented operating system produced by Microsoft to be built on the Windows NT kernel and architecture.

Windows XP was released for retail sale on October 25, 2001, and over 400 million copies were in use in January 2006, according to an estimate in that month by an IDC analyst.
